    "With α <0.01, it can be concluded that GA ED has statistically significantly greater values than GA E. 6-DOF Case StudyAs presented in columns GA E and GA ED of Table 5.2 for the 6-DOF case study, we observe the similar results as CD case study, reinforcing the effectiveness of including diversity as a fitness function in the GA for WCET estimation.The t-tests also confirmed the statistical significance of the differences with p-value close to 0.",
    "So, we reject the null hypothesis.",
    "Therefore, we can conclude that GA ED (GA with both Execution Time and Diversity) has statistically significantly greater values than GA E (GA with only Execution Time).The accompanying boxplot (Figure 5.3) illustrates the broader range of execution times covered by the GA when diversity is included, indicating a more extensive exploration of the solution space.",
    "This approach not only uncovers configurations that lead to higher execution times-suggesting a superior estimation of WCET-but also provides a holistic view of the system's performance under varying conditions, enhancing the reliability of the estimation.",
    "Similar to the CD case study, the results for the 6DOF case study affirm the critical role of diversity in enhancing the GA's ability to identify worst-case scenarios."
